- Enabling an internal right automatically enables the module; removing rights never disables it.
- Dirty indicator in title; styled close-without-save dialog when there are unsaved changes.

## Color Semantics

- Use neutral `background.paper`, `divider`, `action.hover`, and `action.selected` for most surfaces.
- Keep brand `primary` for Save, selected filters, active controls, focus, and a thin selected-navigation indicator.
- Module statuses: success = enabled, warning = enabled without rights, info = always enabled, default gray = disabled.
- Status chips remain outlined and include text; never communicate state by color alone.
- Do not tint the whole card for normal enabled state. Red/error styling is reserved for destructive actions and actual errors.

## Access & Actions

- Respect `canEdit`: disable inputs, hide Save/Copy/Delete.
- Copy/delete: existing styled sub-dialogs; delete blocked when employees are assigned.
- After save/copy/delete: call `onSaved()` and refresh hierarchy from server.

## Mobile

- `fullScreen` dialog on small breakpoints.
- Section list: horizontal scroll chips/tabs on xs instead of tall vertical list when possible.
- Avoid nested scroll traps; one primary scroll region for module cards.

## Do Not

- Do not introduce new visual system or heavy custom `sx` beyond layout/scroll fixes.
- Do not use browser `confirm`.
- Do not invent API fields; follow `EMPLOYEES_API.md`.
